The Dodd City varsity cross country teams competed in Avery on Saturday, August 29. The boys team finished second as a team. Team members include:
Jaden Mahar- 3rd
Landon Allen- 4th
Aaron Munger- 13th
Ethan Barnard-1 7th
Brody Mauppin- 19th
Garrett Morrison- 25th
Ian Baker 30th

The girls team finished fourth as a team. Team members include:
Lindsey Mauppin- 3rd
Kaylen Atchley- 15th
Carson Morrison- 25th
Autumn Brown- 27th
Sonora Wild- 29th
Prairie Wild- 32nd
Tiana Jenkins- 35th
Zoie Hobbs- 36th
Kaylee Freeman- 41st

Both teams will run again on Thursday, September 17 at Miller Grove.

post_text:
VOLLEYBALL GAME üèê
August 11, 2020 at Dodd City High School
Time: 5PM
* Fans, coaches, staff, referees, and players will be pre screened before entering the facility.

* Each school will have a designated seating area for fans.

* Attendance will be limited to 50% capacity in accordance with UIL guidelines.

* Attendees are required to wear face coverings as described in Executive Order GA-29

* Groups will maintain at least six feet of distance from other groups at all times. A "group" is defined as no more than 10 people including the members of the household and those persons who traveled together to the facility.

* Seating will be limited to designated areas.

Bonham Public Library
May 14 at 12:29 PM ¬∑

Are you ready to embark on an adventure?
A Summer Reading Adventure like you have never experienced before?

Imagine your story virtually this summer!

Due to the pandemic we will not be having any live performances at the Armory or Storytime at the Library.

We will be using ReadSquared for our Summer Reading Adventure this summer.
http://bonhamreads.readsquared.com/

You can still register at the library starting June 1. It will be a curbside registration. When you register your kids will get their goody bag.

You also can go to our webiste http://www.bonhamlibrary.net/ to register as well.

When you register please come by and pick up your goody bag. These will be available on June 1st.

All of our programs and events will be on Facebook, on YouTube and on Zoom this summer.

We are looking into having Drive In Movie Nights this summer if we can figure out the sound.

Dodd City ISD- The valedictorian for Dodd City ISD Class of 2020 is Niki Johnson.

Niki is the daughter of Brandon Johnson and Gina Melson. Throughout her four years of high school, Niki has maintained an average of 98.461. She has been involved in extracurricular activities including academic UIL, band, robotics, student government, and the National Technical Honors Society. After graduation, she will attend Southern Arkansas University on a Presidential scholarship.

post_text: On Wednesday, March 4, the Dodd City High School band, the Swarm, competed at Princeton High School‚Äôs Sounds of Spring Concert and Sightreading Contest. The band performed three numbers on stage for three judges, and then played a piece of music they had never seen before for three different judges. All six judges involved awarded the Swarm with scores of 1 (superior), which is the highest rating. Mrs. Wild is proud of all the hard work the musicians have done to prepare for this contest, and feels that this performance, along with the judges‚Äô written critiques, was helpful in preparing the Swarm for its first-ever showing in the UIL Concert and Sightreading Contest next month in Anna.
text: On Wednesday, March 4, the Dodd City High School band, the Swarm, competed at Princeton High School‚Äôs Sounds of Spring Concert and Sightreading Contest.
